sql:
SELECT model_name 
FROM economic_models 
WHERE model_creator_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- 'Top three most recently modified' refers to the models with the highest ranks based on the most recent modification date within their model type;
- 'Reliable data sources' are those with an average reliability score greater than 0.8;
- 'Specific economic conditions' include an interest rate greater than 0.05 and an unemployment rate less than 0.06.

- ARIMA models are a type of time series forecasting model;
- "Frequently accessed" means the model has been accessed more than 5 times;
- "High average forecast value" means the average forecast value is greater than 0.5;
- The primary parameter is the first parameter by name in the parameter list.

sql:
SELECT MAX(average_accuracy) AS highest_average_accuracy
FROM (
  SELECT model_id, AVG(result_accuracy) AS average_accuracy
  FROM model_results
  GROUP BY model_id
) AS model_averages;

